social_posts.post_text: Fall Deer Isle, Maine 2022. Shot on #portra400film
Quick look at shooting fight scenes with the best stunt actors in Nashville.
Some older footage from Iceland 2018 before shooting for reels became a thing and you lose 50 percent of your image.
Another fight scene from a short earlier this year. @jeronbray always choreographs these awesome scenes and I get to show up and try not to mess up my part. Him and @storyofsambrooks killed this.
Reliving @hayleyaugustus.mcgee putting on my jacket hood and playing an Amish woman in the house for 2 weeks straight.
3 tips for shooting food and beverage. Check out @cg_nashville and  @cedarcitybeer if you’re in nashville.

A few years ago in Vietnam @tonythunderbird played catch the duck in a remote town. Luckily I filmed it all.
Live shows are fun because they’re the most forgiving. You have a lot of opportunities and angles to get your shots. IMO at least. @jmwofficial
Been working with folks from the Somali community in nashville the past few years. They always make beautiful subjects.

Got to do something really special on thanksgiving. That was interviewing my almost 100 year old great aunt about her life. Being born in the 1920’s she’s lived in both worlds. The modern and not so modern. It’s like speaking a living piece of history. She had family that had taught in the civil war that she new. We’re really a young country and not so far removed from the past.
Favorite photo I’ve ever taken. Old man walking his rice terrace in Vietnam.

New work with @thomasgoforthmusic “Black and Blue” put Friday.

I started a personal photo project over the summer. I wanted to document the local punk scene happening in Murfreesboro. I’ve had a lot of fun getting to know some of the people there and can’t thank them enough for letting me show up as a stranger and snap these events. Here’s a few I’ve enjoyed so far.

Got to be a part of making one of most interesting videos I’ve ever done over the summer. @jmwofficial had the idea to hook up go pros to their truck and drive around Broadway performing live for everyone. Here’s a little piece of it.
